name: FS
description: Fair Share (on a per capita basis) of the carbon budget for each country.
source: FS( i, t ) = getcolumn( p, i, t ) / sumcolumn( p, t )

name: GS
source: GS( i ) = getcolumn( qCO2, i, tHist ) / sumcolumn( qCO2, tHist )

name: K
description: Carbon intensity for country not in COW
source: K( i, t ) = get( GDPReal, i, t ) / get( qBAU, i, t )

name: CA0
description: Mass of CO2 in atmosphere at pre-industrial times

name: r
description: Historical annual rate of growth of emissions

name: tpsens_gamma_lo
description: Physical constants which determine sensitivities of climate system

description: Physical constants which determine sensitivities of climate system

description: Physical constants which determine sensitivities of climate system

description: Physical constants which determine sensitivities of climate system

description: Physical constants which determine sensitivities of climate system

name: T
description:
Link between temperature increase since pre-industrial times and all-time carbon emissions.
Define T = lambda(tpsens) / 
(1 – 
	5.35*lambda(tpsens)*gamma(tpsens)/
		CA0 + Ap(tpsens) * Q
)*
(5.35*ln(1 + Ap(tpsens)*Q/CA0)
+ RNP);	

From Excel 

(lambdamid/(1-(5.35*lambdamid*gammamid)/(CA0 + Apmid*A42)) ) * (5.35 * LN(1+ (Apmid*$A42/CA0) ) + RNP )

Temp(Q) = ( tpsens_lambda_mid / ( 1.0 - (5.35*tpsens_lambda_mid*tpsens_gamma_mid)/(CA0 + tpsens_Ap_mid*Q) ) ) * ( 5.35 * log( tpsens_Ap_mid * Q / CA0 )  ) + RNP

T(Q) =  ( tpsens_lambda / ( 1.0 - ( 5.35 * tpsens_lambda * tpsens_gamma ) / ( CA0 + tpsens_Ap * Q )  )  ) * ( 5.35 * log( 1.0 + ( tpsens_Ap * Q / CA0  ) , e ) + RNP )

name: SafeCarbonBudget
description:
Determine the safe carbon budget according to temperature target chosen by user

2643880422795
source: SafeCarbonBudget( target_temperature ) = goalseek( T, target_temperature, 0, 2000000 )

name: QtoCO2
description: All-time carbon budget converted to units of carbon dioxide

name: E
description: Emissions of carbon dioxide in every year as determined by emissions pathway function (for the world).
source: E(t) = ifElse( t <= tHist, sumcolumn(qCO2, t), ifElse( t <= tM, Em() * exp( r * ( t - tM ) ), Em() * (1 + (r + m) * (t - tM) ) * exp(-m* (t - tM)) ) )

name: tpsens_gamma
description: Effect of climate change on CO2 fluxes (including release of carbon from previously undisturbed pools).

name: tpsens_Ap
description: Effect of increasing CO2 on partition of carbon between atmospheric, land and ocean reservoirs.

name: transf
description: transfers of allowances between countries. Negative values mean a country is supplying allowances to the market.
source: transf( i,t ) = abat( i,t ) - domAbat( i,t )

name: flow
source: flow(i,t) =( abat(i,t) - domAbat(i,t)  ) * wpEQ(t)

name: alpha
description: Calculates the convergence parameter alpha(t) according to the date of convergence chosen by the user.
source: alpha(t) = ifElse( t <= tC, ( t - tHist ) / ( tC - tHist ), 1.0 )

name: qBar
description:
Calculates the allowances of each country at each year so that they converge to their fair share.

qBar(i,t) = E(t) * ((alpha(t)*FS(i,t)) + (1- alpha(t))*GS(i))
source: qBar(i,t) = ifElse( allocation_rule == 0, E(t) * ( (alpha(t)*FS(i,t)) + (1- alpha(t))*GS(i) ), ifElse( allocation_rule == 2,  E(t) * ( (alpha(t)*FS(i,t)) + (1- alpha(t))*GDPS(i, t)), 666 ) )

name: abat
description:
Each country’s abatement target

abat( i, t ) = getcolumn( qBAU, i, t ) - qBar( i, t )
source: abat( i, t ) = getcolumn( qBAU, i, t ) - qBar( i, t )

name: Em
description:
Emissions in the year at which mitigation starts (projected using BAU).
Em() = sumcolumn( qBAU, tM )
Em() = getcolumn( qWLD, i, t - 1) * (1 + r)
source: Em() = sumcolumn( qWLDBAU, tM )

name: F
source: F(m) = kQtHist + (( ( Em() - Em() *exp( r * ( tHist - tM ) ) ) / r ) + ( Em() * ( -(exp( m * ( tM - tFut ) ) )* ( m * ( ( m + r ) * ( tFut - tM ) + 2 ) + r ) + 2 * m  + r ) ) / (m ^ 2 ))  - kQCO2

name: kQtHist
description:
Temporary precalculation of cumulative historical CO2 emissions 

old = 1304145333333
new = 2437000000000

name: FPrime
source: FPrime(m) = ( - (1/(m^3)) * Em() * ((tM-tFut)*(tFut-tM) * (m^3) * exp((tM-tFut)*m) + (tM-tFut)*(m^2) * exp((tM-tFut)*m) * ((tFut-tM)*r+2) + m * (exp((tM-tFut)*m) * ((tM-tFut)*r - (tFut-tM)*r -2) +2) -2*r * (exp((tM-tFut)*m)-1)))

name: findmitigationrate
source: findmitigationrate() = newtonraphson( F, FPrime, 100, 0.000001 )

name: QtFutPreM
description: sum of CO2 emission pre mitigation, this should be calculated from mitigation date selected by user

name: QCO2
description: Takes the all-time safe carbon budget and spread it out over the years into a safe emissions pathway (make the bell curve)
source: QCO2(t) = ifElse( t <= tHist, sumcolumn( qCO2, t ), ifElse( t < tM, Em() * exp( r * ( t - tM ) ), Em() * ( 1 + ( r + m ) * ( t - tM ) ) * exp( -m * ( t - tM ) ) ) )

name: regul
description: Amount of the abatement target is met by domestic decarbonisation
source: regul(i , t ) = ifElse( trading_scenario == endogenous_regulation, regulated_share, 100 )

name: totalcost
description: Total costs of participating in a trading scheme are costs of decarbonisation plus any flows (minus or plus). If flows are negative, this represents revenue from trading which offsets the costs of decarbonisation.
source: totalcost( i,t ) = flow( i,t ) + decarbcost( i,t )

name: calculateQtPreM
source: calculateQtPreM() = ( Em() - Em() * exp( r * ( tHist - tM ) ) ) /r

name: calculateQtHist
source: calculateQtHist() = numintegrate( E, 1751, 2013 )

name: cumulativeemissions
source: cumulativeemissions(t) = QtHist + numintegrate( E, tHist, t )

name: bauemissions
source: bauemissions( i, t ) = getcolumn( qBAU, i, t )

name: countryemissions
description:
Country emissions on emissions pathway

countryemissions(i,t) = ifElse( t <= tHist, getcolumn(qCO2, i,t), ifElse( t <= tM, getcolumn(qBAU, i,t) * exp( r * ( t - tM ) ), getcolumn(qBAU, i,t)* (1 + (r + m) * (t - tM) ) * exp(-m* (t - tM)) ) )

countryemissions(i,t) = ifElse( trading_scenario == 3,  getcolumn( qBAU, i, t ) - abat( i, t ) , ifElse( trading_scenario == 1,  qBar( i, t ), ifElse( trading_scenario == 0,  getcolumn( qBAU, i, t ) - abat( i, t ), getcolumn( qBAU, i, t )  - ( transf( i, t ) + domAbat( i, t ) ) ) )
source: countryemissions(i,t) = ifElse( trading_scenario == 0,  qBar( i,t ) + transf( i,t  ), ifElse( trading_scenario == 2,  getcolumn( qBAU, i, t )  - ( domAbat( i, t ) + transf( i, t ) ), qBar( i, t ) ) )

name: decarbcostGDP
description: Decarbonisation costs as a share of GDP as %
source: decarbcostGDP( i,t ) = ( decarbcost( i,t ) / getcolumn( GDPReal, i, t ) )*100

name: HistoricalRespDate

name: WorldHistE
description:
Global historical emissions counted from time of historical responsibilities date
WorldHistE(i) = sumrowbounds( qWLD, 0 ) 
WorldHistE(i, t) =  sum( qCO2, t ) - wld emissions in 2013 when eval at 0,2013
source: WorldHistE(i,t) =  multiply( sumrow(qCO2, i) , sumcolumn(qCO2, t) )

name: CO2owed
source: CO2owed(i ,t ) = FS( i, t ) * WorldHistE() - getcolumn( qCO2, i , t)

name: HistE
source: HistE(i) = sumrowbounds( qCO2, i )

name: GDPS
source: GDPS( i, t ) = getcolumn( GDPReal, i, t ) / sumcolumn( GDPReal, t )

name: totalcostGDP

source: totalcostGDP( i,t ) = ( totalcost( i,t ) / getcolumn( GDPReal, i, t ) )*100

source: emissionscapita( i,t ) = ( countryemissions( i,t ) / getcolumn( p, i, t ) )

name: flowGDP

name: allowancescapita
source: allowancescapita( i,t ) = ( qBar( i,t ) / getcolumn( p, i, t ) )
